If you’re just starting out with music or are ready to take it more seriously, here are some steps to start with 👇🏻

1. Getting set up with a website may be daunting at first, but then you'll actually get to OWN your content. Regardless of social media trends, your website will be a constant. This is also a great, professional place to send future fans and clients! 

2. It's easy to spend money on gear, instruments, etc. but sometimes musicians don't take the "business" side as seriously when it comes to investing. Don't be afraid to put some money down on a website, copyright fees or educational courses. 

3. This is what helps you find your "tribe," or fans that stick with you through it all. Just be YOU; the things that make you YOU are what makes you original and unique from other artists. 

4. Don't pressure yourself to reach "success" in the first few months of starting out! You will burn yourself out quickly if you're rushing to "get to the top." There is no race, so take your time and go at your own pace. Don't make unrealistic goals or you're setting yourself up for disappointment.

5. Treat your fans like friends! Don't ignore them - make sure to truly engage and give more than a "hello!" or "thanks!"

6. Make sure to always be learning! There's always something new to learn - don't think that you know it all. Try out an e-course, sign up for email lists that bring your music industry news, watch YouTube videos on songwriting tips, etc. Doing this will only help you!

Monetize Your Music with These Creative Strategies 👇

Finding it challenging to earn from your music? Let's explore some practical ways to turn your creative output into income:

1️⃣ Maximize Your Social Media Platforms 
Go live regularly, share performances, talk about your merchandise, and pin your website link. Engaging directly with your audience can lead to immediate sales. Remember, personal connections drive commerce.

2️⃣ Embrace Authentic Music Videos 
Worried about the high cost of music videos? Your phone's camera is more powerful than you think. Create raw, one-take videos that focus on the emotion and authenticity of your performance. Often, the raw energy and sincerity of such videos resonate more with audiences than high-budget productions.

3️⃣ Bundle Merch with Music 
Got merchandise that's not selling? Bundle it with your music. Offer exclusive song downloads with each merchandise purchase. This strategy adds value to your products and gives fans an incentive to buy, making them feel they're getting something special and unique.

4️⃣ Explore Sync Licensing Opportunities 
Frustrated with low royalty earnings? Delve into the world of sync licensing. Getting your music featured in films, commercials, and TV shows can be a significant source of income. Start by collaborating with independent filmmakers and content creators to build your portfolio and gain exposure.
